Package coloradocollege.ifroning

Class Summary
Activator An activator is any object that the player can interact with that is not an item.
ActivatorList An activator list is a list of activators stored in an array.
Command Interprets a string of text as a command and attempts to follow it.
GameFrame The frame in which the game is played - contains an input field and an output area.
Inventory An inventory is a list of items stored in an array.
Item An item has a name.
Key A key is an item that is used on an activator.
Location A location has a static description, activators that may change in state and items that may be added or removed.
LocationInventory A location inventory is a specialized inventory meant to be used with a specific location.
Player A player has a name, location and inventory.
PlayerInventory A player inventory is a specialized inventory that is assigned to a player.
Potion A potion is a specialized item that can be used on the player.
Runner Runs the game.
Teleporter A teleporter is a specialized item that moves the player from their current location to a new location.
TesterCLI Tests the project without using the GUI.
TesterGUI Tests the project using the GUI.
